value.displayForm: RVF 114 and 136-38 have been cancelled with some strokes of pen.
18th/19th century Italian full parchment over boards with pink marbled endpapers; red and green leather spine labels with gilt lettering.
Signature of Walter L. Bullock on inside upper cover
Donated to the The University of Manchester by Hélène Louise Bullock, the widow of Walter L. Bullock, Serena Professor of Italian, in 1944.

Recorded in University of Manchester Library Search
A link to the AHRC Petrarch database will be put here

title.displayForm: Il Petrarcha con l’espositione d’Allessandro Vellutello di novo ristampato con le figure a i triomphi, et con piu cose utili in varii luoghi aggiunte.
title.label: Title

value.displayForm: Poems in italic type and commentary in roman type; printed numbering; most of Petrarch’s texts set on left in small block, with commentary distributed on three sides; some other Petrarch’s texts set on left in a sequence of blocks, with commentary distributed in single column on right. Title within architectural frame; one full-page woodcut (map) on *5v, one small woodcut (portrait) on *2v, six rectangular-box woodcuts (Triumfi: X2r, Z4v, AA1r, AA7r, CC3v, CC6r.

title.displayForm: Small woodcut with an urn with half-length portraits of Laura and Petrarch facing each other; sonnet on Petrarch and Laura’s ashes, ‘Laura, ch’un Sol fu tra le Donne in terra’ (‘Sonetto sopra le sacre ceneri del Petrarcha e di M. Laura’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Vellutello’s life of Petrarch (‘Vita e costumi del poeta’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Full-page topographical map of Provence
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Life of Laura with a description of Vaucluse (‘Origine di Madonna Laura con la descrittione de Valclusa, e del luogo ove il poeta a principio di lei s’innamorò’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Discussion of how RVF is divided into three parts (‘Divisione de son. e de le canz. del Petrarcha in tre parti’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: First part of RVF with commentary (‘Sonetti, e canzoni del divino poeta M. Francesco Petrarca, colla espositione di M. Alessandro Vellutello’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Second part of RVF (beginning with RVF 267) with commentary (‘Sonetti, e canzoni del divino poeta Messer Francesco Petrarcha in morte di madonna Laura colla espositione del Vellutello’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Third part of RVF with commentary (‘Incomincia la terza parte de i sonetti et delle canzoni di M. Francesco Petrarcha, colla espositione di Messer Alessandro Vellutello’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Poems addressed to Petrarch by Muzio Stramazzo da Perugia (‘La santa fiamma, de laqual son priue’), Giacomo Colonna (‘Se le parti del corpo mio destrutte’), Geri Gianfigliazzi (‘Messer Francesco, chi d’amor sospira’), and Giovanni Dondi dall’Orologio (‘Io non so ben s’io uedo quel, ch’io ueggio’), each poem is followed by the first line of Petrarch’s reply accompanied by the page number where the poem is printed; Vellutello’s prologue to his commentary on the Triumphi (‘Alessandro Vellutello sopra i Triomphi del Petrarca’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Vellutello’s overview of the content of the Triumphi (‘Soggetto de’ Triomphi del poeta’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Triumphi with commentary (‘Triomphi di messer Francesco Petrarca, colla espositione di messer Alessandro Vellutello’); each triumph is preceded by a rectangular-box woodcut: Triumphus Amoris (X2r); Triumphus Pudicitie (Z4v), Triumphus Mortis (AA1r), Triumphus Fame (AA7r), Triumphus Temporis (CC3v), Triumphus Divinitatis (CC6r)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Petrarch’s scattered poems (capitolo ‘Nel cor pien d’amarissima dolcezza’, canzone ‘Quel, c’ha nostra natura in se piu degno’, ballad ‘Noua bellezza in habito gentile’, sonnet ‘Anima doue sei? ch’adhora adhora’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Poems addressed to Petrarch by Jacopo de’ Caratori da Imola (‘O nouella Tarpea, in cui s’asconde’) and Ser Diotesalvi di Pietro da Siena (‘Il bello occhio d’Apollo, del cui sguardo’), each poem is followed by Petrarch’s reply (‘Ingegno usato a le question profonde’ and ‘Se Phebo al primo amor non è bugiardo’, respectively)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Petrarch’s scattered sonnets (‘Quella ghirlanda, che la bella fronte’, ‘Stato fuss’io, quando la uidi prima’, ‘In ira a i cieli, al mondo, & a la gente’, ‘Se sotto legge Amor uiuesse quella’, ‘Lasso com’io fui mal approueduto’, and ‘Quella, che ’l giouenil mio cor auinse’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Alphabetical index of the first lines of both RVF poems and the Triumphi’s capitoli (under each letter of the alphabet sonnets and canzoni (including capitoli) are listed separately, both according to their order of appearance) (‘Tavola de son. et de le canz. del Petrarcha’)
title.label: Title

title.displayForm: Register; printer’s mark; colophon: In Vinegia appresso Gabriel Giolito de Ferrari e fratelli MDLII
title.label: Title
